<BR><BR>Tablets CW 3446-58 involved in this invention were also compared to a comparable product that does not contain the L-HPC.  LH21 disintegrant; i.e., tablets CY 3513-1 (see Table III), as to their dissolution rate at various conditions of storage
and in different types of containers.  In addition, they were also compared as to their stability as measured by the FSA values.  These measurements were made after 2 months storage.  The results of these studies are summarized in Table V below.
